According to the [[w:documentary hypothesis|documentary hypothesis]], the [[w:Torah|Torah]] is composed from a number of originally independent sources joined by a [[w:redaction|redactor]]. One of these supposed sources is named the [[w:Jahwist|"Jahwist source"]], due to its preference of referring to God as [[w:Yahweh|Yahweh]] (usually translated as "The LORD"). This prose source contains within it two poems thought to have been earlier separate sources - the [[w:Song of the Sea|Song of the Sea]], and the [[w:Blessing of Jacob|Blessing of Jacob]].

There follows the reconstructed text of the Jahwist Source, using the [[w:King James Version|King James Translation]] of the Torah. 
