{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|2}}{{font|color=#000000| And Abimelech said unto Isaac, Go from us; for thou art much mightier than we.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|3}}{{font|color=#000000| And Isaac departed thence, and pitched his tent in the valley of Gerar, and dwelt there.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|4}}{{font|color=#000000| And Isaac's servants digged in the valley, and found there a well of springing water.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|5}}{{font|color=#000000| And the herdmen of Gerar did strive with Isaac's herdmen, saying, The water is ours: and he called the name of the well Esek; because they strove with him.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|6}}{{font|color=#000000| And they digged another well, and strove for that also: and he called the name of it Sitnah.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|7}}{{font|color=#000000| And he removed from thence, and digged another well; and for that they strove not: and he called the name of it Rehoboth; and he said, For now the LORD hath made room for us, and we shall be fruitful in the land.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|8}}{{font|color=#000000| And he went up from thence to Beersheba.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|9}}{{font|color=#000000| And the LORD appeared unto him the same night, and said, I am the God of Abraham thy father: fear not, for I am with thee, and will bless thee, and multiply thy seed for my servant Abraham's sake.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|10}}{{font|color=#000000| And he builded an altar there, and called upon the name of the LORD, and pitched his tent there: and there Isaac's servants digged a well.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|11}}{{font|color=#000000| Then Abimelech went to him from Gerar, and Ahuzzath one of his friends, and Phichol the chief captain of his army.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|12}}{{font|color=#000000| And Isaac said unto them, Wherefore come ye to me, seeing ye hate me, and have sent me away from you?}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|13}}{{font|color=#000000| And they said, We saw certainly that the LORD was with thee: and we said, Let there be now an oath betwixt us, even betwixt us and thee, and let us make a covenant with thee;}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|14}}{{font|color=#000000| That thou wilt do us no hurt, as we have not touched thee, and as we have done unto thee nothing but good, and have sent thee away in peace: thou art now the blessed of the LORD.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|15}}{{font|color=#000000| And he made them a feast, and they did eat and drink.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|16}}{{font|color=#000000| And they rose up betimes in the morning, and sware one to another: and Isaac sent them away, and they departed from him in peace.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|17}}{{font|color=#000000| And it came to pass the same day, that Isaac's servants came, and told him concerning the well which they had digged, and said unto him, We have found water.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|18}}{{font|color=#000000| And he called it Shebah: therefore the name of the city is Beersheba unto this day.}}

