==Joseph enslaved==

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|1}}{{font|color=#000000|Now Israel loved Joseph more than all his children, because he was the son of his old age: and he made him a coat of many colours.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|2}}{{font|color=#000000|And when his brethren saw that their father loved him more than all his brethren, they hated him, and could not speak peaceably unto him.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|3}}{{font|color=#000000| And Joseph dreamed a dream, and he told it his brethren: and they hated him yet the more.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|4}}{{font|color=#000000| And he said unto them, Hear, I pray you, this dream which I have dreamed:}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|5}}{{font|color=#000000| For, behold, we were binding sheaves in the field, and, lo, my sheaf arose, and also stood upright; and, behold, your sheaves stood round about, and made obeisance to my sheaf.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|6}}{{font|color=#000000| And his brethren said to him, Shalt thou indeed reign over us? or shalt thou indeed have dominion over us? And they hated him yet the more for his dreams, and for his words.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|7}}{{font|color=#000000| And he dreamed yet another dream, and told it his brethren, and said, Behold, I have dreamed a dream more; and, behold, the sun and the moon and the eleven stars made obeisance to me.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|8}}{{font|color=#000000| And he told it to his father, and to his brethren: and his father rebuked him, and said unto him, What is this dream that thou hast dreamed? Shall I and thy mother and thy brethren indeed come to bow down ourselves to thee to the earth?}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|9}}{{font|color=#000000| And his brethren envied him, and they said one to another, Behold, this dreamer cometh.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|10}}{{font|color=#000000| Come now therefore, and let us slay him, and cast him into some pit, and we will say, Some evil beast hath devoured him: and we shall see what will become of his dreams.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|11}}{{font|color=#000000| And it came to pass, when Joseph was come unto his brethren, that they stript Joseph out of his coat, his coat of many colours that was on him;}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|12}}{{font|color=#000000| And they lifted up their eyes and looked, and, behold, a company of Ishmeelites came from Gilead with their camels bearing spicery and balm and myrrh, going to carry it down to Egypt.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|13}}{{font|color=#000000| And Judah said unto his brethren, What profit is it if we slay our brother, and conceal his blood?}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|14}}{{font|color=#000000| Come, and let us sell him to the Ishmeelites, and let not our hand be upon him; for he is our brother and our flesh. And his brethren were content.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|15}}{{font|color=#000000| And sold Joseph to the Ishmeelites for twenty pieces of silver: and they brought Joseph into Egypt.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|16}}{{font|color=#000000| And they took Joseph's coat, and killed a kid of the goats, and dipped the coat in the blood;}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|17}}{{font|color=#000000| And they sent the coat of many colours, and they brought it to their father; and said, This have we found: know now whether it be thy son's coat or no.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|18}}{{font|color=#000000| And he knew it, and said, It is my son's coat; an evil beast hath devoured him; Joseph is without doubt rent in pieces.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|19}}{{font|color=#000000| And Jacob rent his clothes, and put sackcloth upon his loins, and mourned for his son many days.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|20}}{{font|color=#000000| And all his sons and all his daughters rose up to comfort him; but he refused to be comforted; and he said, For I will go down into the grave unto my son mourning. Thus his father wept for him.}}

==Judah and Tamar==

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|1}}{{font|color=#000000| And it came to pass at that time, that Judah went down from his brethren, and turned in to a certain Adullamite, whose name was Hirah.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|2}}{{font|color=#000000| And Judah saw there a daughter of a certain Canaanite, whose name was Shuah; and he took her, and went in unto her.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|3}}{{font|color=#000000| And she conceived, and bare a son; and he called his name Er.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|4}}{{font|color=#000000| And she conceived again, and bare a son; and she called his name Onan.}}

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|5}}{{font|color=#000000| And she yet again conceived, and bare a son; and called his name Shelah: and he was at Chezib, when she bare him.}}

